
This web application is designed to provide real-time visualizations of Bitcoin close price data sourced from a local PostgreSQL database. The application features two primary plots: a histogram and a line plot, both of which dynamically update to reflect the data over time.

Key Features:
Real-Time Data Integration: The application continuously fetches live Bitcoin close price data from the PostgreSQL database, ensuring that users have access to the most current information.

Dynamic Histogram: The histogram visualizes the distribution of close prices over time, providing insights into market trends and fluctuations.

Real-Time Line Plot: A line plot displays the close prices over time, enabling users to monitor price movements and identify patterns in the data.

Purpose:
The primary objective of this application is to visually represent the distribution of Bitcoin close price data in real time, facilitating further analysis and decision-making processes for users engaged in cryptocurrency trading and investment.
